DataElement.preferredName: Clinical Performed Observation Outcome Report Date and Time ISO21090.TS.DATETIME.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A result of a clinical observation, i.e. from an examination, test or direct observation performed on the subject. EXAMPLE(S): The performed observation of "WBC count" would be associated to a clinical result called "WBC result" in which the results of the observation (13000 WBCs) would be stored. The date (and time) on which the result is reported.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Clinical Performed Observation Outcome Report Date and Time
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Relating to the examination and treatment of patients dependent on direct observation.  The term may also refer to the institution (clinic) providing this activity.:Executed and carried through to completion.:Watching something and taking note of what happens.:The result of an action._A short textual account; having provided a short account.:An expression of both date and time that an event has happened or will happen.
